Remarks were given by Vice President Mike Pence at the White House on the eve of Cinco de Mayo. He expressed his gratitude towards the Hispanic community and highlighted the contributions made by Mexican Americans and Hispanic Americans to the United States. Pence also discussed the Trump administration's efforts to empower Hispanic Americans and promote policies that create jobs and opportunities for all Americans. He mentioned the recent passage of the healthcare reform bill in the House of Representatives and the upcoming tax cuts. Pence emphasized the importance of education and the administration's commitment to providing access to quality education for all Americans. He concluded by stating that the future is bright for Hispanic Americans and Americans of every background under the leadership of President Donald Trump.